copy (incomplete), <span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ U.S. Library of Congress, Washington, D.C. ]">DLC</span>: John David Woelpper Letter Book.
</p>

</div>
<div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-09-02-0295-fn-0001-ptr" id="GEWN-02-09-02-0295-fn-0001">1</a>

   <p>Letter not found.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-09-02-0295-fn-0002-ptr" id="GEWN-02-09-02-0295-fn-0002">2</a>

   <p>The orders of the Virginia council to which GW refers are printed in <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-09-02-0283&amp;expandNote=GEWN-02-09-02-0283-fn-0005#GEWN-02-09-02-0283-fn-0005" class="document">GW to Lord Dunmore and Council, c.3 Nov., n.5</a>.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-09-02-0295-fn-0003-ptr" id="GEWN-02-09-02-0295-fn-0003">3</a>

   <p>For a discussion of Thomas Bullitts surveying expedition down the Ohio in the summer of 1773, see <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-09-02-0188" class="document">John Connolly to GW, 29 June 1773</a>, and <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-09-02-0188&amp;expandNote=GEWN-02-09-02-0188-fn-0006#GEWN-02-09-02-0188-fn-0006" class="document">note 6 of that document</a>. Wilper had accompanied Bullitt on his surveying expedition. See <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-09-02-0238" class="document">Connolly to GW, 29 Aug. 1773</a>.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-09-02-0295-fn-0004-ptr" id="GEWN-02-09-02-0295-fn-0004">4</a>

   <p>The letter-book copy has rendered this as Ponticello.</p>

</div>
<span class="pb center" title="page number in print edition (no page scan available)" id="GEWN-02-09-02-pb-0393">[393]</span>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-09-02-0295-fn-0005-ptr" id="GEWN-02-09-02-0295-fn-0005">5</a>

   <p>See <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-09-02-0283" class="document">GW to Lord Dunmore and Council, c.3 November</a>. Wilpers letter-book copy ends here.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-09-02-0295-fn-0006-ptr" id="GEWN-02-09-02-0295-fn-0006">6</a>

   <p>See <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-09-02-0207" class="document">Advertisement of Western Lands, 15 July 1773</a>, and <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-09-02-0207&amp;expandNote=GEWN-02-09-02-0207-sn#GEWN-02-09-02-0207-sn" class="document">its source note</a><span class="choice deletion" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover_choice ] header=[]  body=[ Deleted: ', printed above' &lt;span style='font-size: 90%'&gt;[[2014-11-24]]&lt;/span&gt; ]"><img alt="deletion" src="images/deletion_mark-trans.png" style="border:none;vertical-align: text-bottom; padding-right:2px"/></span>.</p>

